name: Norfolk County Public Library
directions:
The first bathroom is in Backroom with the non-fiction books on the right of the kids shelf which is behind the table near the entrance to the backroom.

 The second bathroom is upstairs in the kids area (turn right) in the top corner next to that little mini kids room. If you are unable to walk up the stairs, take the elevator.
comment: All you have to do is walk in, ask the front desk person for the bathroom key, and head to the bathroom.

name: Norfolk County Public Library
directions:
The first bathroom is in the backroom with the non-fiction books, next to the shelf of kids non-fiction books.

 The second one is upstairs in the back corner of the kids area, there's an elevator if you aren't able to walk up the stairs
comment: It's a library so you can just head in there and ask the person at the front desk for the key to the bathroom. The downstairs bathroom is immediately accessible to everyone.
